put the hard word on
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:to ask a favour or a loan; (to a woman, or homosexual) to ask for sexual favours;  cf. put the bite on.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1949 (Wellington) The way they're wooing in the bedroom looks like he'll soon be putting the hard word across her.
